## 🌍 Where Is This Used?
Splitting a data word into byte-aligned segments is one of the most common operations in digital hardware. It appears in:

- **Bus & Memory Interfaces** — breaking wide data buses into byte-addressable segments for memory access
- **Communication Protocols** — separating header/payload bytes in packet-based data formats (UART, SPI, I2C frame handling)
- **Data Serialization** — converting parallel data into byte-wise streams for transmission
- **Processor Datapaths** — splitting register or instruction words into opcode/operand byte fields

